gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 117, Nuggets 107
gameRecap.excerpt: After overcoming a 22 points deficit from the 2nd quarter to tie the game and force OT, the Nuggets were outscored 15-5 in OT and lost to the Suns, 117-107. Kevin Durant led the Suns with 35 points (14-34 FG), eight rebounds, and five assists as Grayson Allen added 28 points (8-12 3PT). Jamal Murray (28 points, seven rebounds, nine assists) and Nikola Jokic (25 points, 16 rebounds, five assists) led the Nuggets in defeat. Suns snap a two-game skid to improve to 36-26 as the Nuggets have their six-game W streak snapped, move to 42-20.
